<p>One important point to note is :-</p>

<p>let there are two functions :-</p>

<pre><code>sum(1,2);

const sum = function(first, second) {
  return first + second;
}
</code></pre>

<p>In above case, it will give error that sum is not defined, but</p>

<pre><code>sum(1,2);

function sum(first, second) {
  return first + second;
}
</code></pre>

<p>This function will not any error as <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Glossary/Hoisting" rel="nofollow noreferrer">Hoisting</a> will take place in this case.</p>
